headline: Does Stronger Non‑GAAP Profit and New Debt Shelf Change The Bull Case For Hormel Foods (HRL)?
summary: In the past few weeks, Hormel Foods reported full-year 2025 results showing sales of US$12.11 billion but sharply lower earnings, issued fiscal 2026 guidance, completed a long-running US$555.78 million share repurchase program, and filed a shelf registration for new senior unsecured debt securities. Despite pressured consumer demand and input cost inflation, management highlighted stronger-than-expected non-GAAP profit and ongoing Transform and Modernize cost initiatives aimed at supporting...

headline: Costco issues urgent recall on nuts
summary: A new food recall is issued by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) at least once a week. The recalls are related to allergens, possible bacterial or lead contaminations, and the potential presence of glass, wood, plastic or other foreign material that should not be in our food.
